1
00:00:01,340 --> 00:00:03,810
- Oh, no, it was nothing.
- Don't say that.

2
00:00:03,880 --> 00:00:05,910
- Goodness...
- That's right.

3
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:07,980
- Honestly.
- I'm so embarrassed.

4
00:00:08,110 --> 00:00:12,120
Han Young Ja, you're just thrilled
to have your son and daughter-in-law here.

5
00:00:12,450 --> 00:00:13,520
Good grief.

6
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:16,860
Dad, come and eat.

7
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:20,230
- I'm fine.
- What do you mean you're fine?

8
00:00:20,490 --> 00:00:23,830
- Come on, eat with us. Hurry.
- I said I'm fine.

9
00:00:24,030 --> 00:00:27,170
Mom, it's all ready. Please, have a seat.

10
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:29,730
Goodness.

11
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,870
I told you
we should've just ordered delivery.

12
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:36,040
You really didn't have to go
to all this trouble.

13
00:00:37,310 --> 00:00:39,840
I wanted to cook with you.

14
00:00:39,980 --> 00:00:44,420
I wanted to cook
a heartfelt meal for you...

15
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:47,920
for raising Baek Ho to be
such a wonderful and upstanding man.

16
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:52,160
To think I didn't realize
what a sweet and kind person you were,

17
00:00:52,690 --> 00:00:54,530
and I was so against you two
getting married.

18
00:00:55,760 --> 00:01:01,070
You know I drove a stake
through your father's heart back then.

19
00:01:01,830 --> 00:01:04,200
I'm so sorry for what I did back then.

20
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:07,940
I want to formally apologize
to you, Jang Mi.

21
00:01:09,510 --> 00:01:12,580
- Mother, you don't have to be so formal.
- Alright!

22
00:01:13,410 --> 00:01:15,910
We can't eat
while you're sitting there, Dad.

23
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:16,950
Come on.

24
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:20,650
- Hello.
- Have a seat.

25
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:22,520
Sit down, you guys.

26
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:32,500
This looks delicious.

27
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:34,900
What is it?

28
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:38,000
Worried you won't be able to stomach it?

29
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:40,670
What?

30
00:01:40,740 --> 00:01:41,910
You know what I'm talking about.

31
00:01:42,740 --> 00:01:46,910
You have to sit here facing
and eating the stew made...

32
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:49,980
by the daughter of the man
you drove to his death.

33
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,280
You must be asking yourself,
"What kind of sick joke is this?"

34
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,120
Ha Young Ja.

35
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:59,160
Do you really have to talk
like that at the dinner table...

36
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,430
to feel satisfied?

37
00:02:01,490 --> 00:02:02,890
Am I wrong?

38
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:05,400
Blinded by some other woman...

39
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:09,430
- What did you just say?
- Mom, Dad,

40
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:10,900
please, just stop.

41
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:13,810
Must you really act this way
in front of Jang Mi?

42
00:02:15,070 --> 00:02:17,240
No, it's okay. I'm fine, Baek Ho.

43
00:02:20,010 --> 00:02:23,180
Please excuse me for a moment.

44
00:02:33,290 --> 00:02:34,290
Hey, Tae Pyung.

45
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,330
Hey, grab some ice cream on your way back.

46
00:02:36,330 --> 00:02:37,800
Mom won't stop nagging me about it.

47
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:40,700
Suk Hee wants ice cream.

48
00:02:41,070 --> 00:02:43,570
Me too! Auntie, bring back a lot, okay?

49
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,370
Okay, got it.

50
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,140
Bye.

51
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:59,050
(Forensic Science)

52
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:09,830
I'm so sorry, Jang Mi.

53
00:03:10,530 --> 00:03:12,760
My parents were completely out of line.

54
00:03:13,770 --> 00:03:14,800
It's okay.

55
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:18,470
So this is your room.

56
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,840
You're right.
This is your first time in here, right?

57
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:24,980
Yes. It's totally you.

58
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,010
Bright and a little mischievous.

59
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:29,510
It's not normally this messy.

60
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:33,450
My dad's been staying in here
since my mom kicked him out,

61
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:35,120
so it's a bit of a disaster zone.

62
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,760
That's just life.

63
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:40,830
Seeing my parents live
in separate rooms...

64
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:44,030
really made me realize
that I never want to live like that.

65
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:46,560
- What?
- Let's promise to never sleep separately,

66
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,000
no matter how much we fight.

67
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:52,070
Even if we're mad and sleep back-to-back,
we will always be in the same bed.

68
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:53,070
Okay?

69
00:03:58,610 --> 00:04:00,610
- We can't.
- Come on.

70
00:04:01,980 --> 00:04:03,050
Goodness.

71
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:05,820
Hey now, loving each other isn't a crime!

72
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:07,690
Don't mind me and go for it.

73
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:09,550
Let's go.

74
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:20,570
Mother.

75
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:24,300
I should probably get going now.
I'll come visit again soon.

76
00:04:25,270 --> 00:04:27,540
What? You haven't even finished eating.

77
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:34,110
Come visit often.

78
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,280
I'll give her a ride.

79
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:38,450
Let's go, Jang Mi.

80
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:57,370
I have to take care of myself
if I'm going to see our Eun Hye.

81
00:04:58,470 --> 00:04:59,470
That's right.

82
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:04,710
This old body has to hold on
so I can hug my poor daughter.

83
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:12,380
Chairman, I believe we've found her.

84
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:14,390
We've finally found her.

85
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:17,220
What? You found her?

86
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,520
You...

87
00:05:20,090 --> 00:05:22,790
found my daughter, Eun Hye?

88
00:05:35,970 --> 00:05:36,970
Come.

89
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:41,950
What? They found her?

90
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,920
Don't tell me they found Jung Suk Hee.

91
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:47,450
This can't be happening.

92
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,550
They can't find Jung Suk Hee yet!

93
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,590
I can't just sit around.

94
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,400
Who on earth is it?

95
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:08,840
Who is Chairman Ma's biological daughter?

96
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:12,640
It can't be Jung Suk Hee. Absolutely not.

97
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:16,150
What? You found a Park Young Mi?

98
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,080
My daughter, Park Young Mi?

99
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:20,520
It's a very common name in Korea.

100
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:25,720
But we looked into every Park Young Mi
of the right age from an orphanage.

101
00:06:25,790 --> 00:06:28,830
So, are you saying you found her?

102
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:32,230
Yes, we found a woman named Park Young Mi
working in a restaurant,

103
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,670
and she confirmed she was
in an orphanage as a child.

104
00:06:35,570 --> 00:06:36,600
Goodness.

105
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,470
He found his biological daughter already?

106
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,340
This is bad.

107
00:06:41,670 --> 00:06:45,540
Hong Ju, the Chairman found his daughter.
What are we going to do?

108
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:48,850
What? He found his daughter that quickly?

109
00:06:49,710 --> 00:06:53,220
So, what happened? Tell me more.

110
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:55,620
I asked if she had any childhood photos
she could show me.

111
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:57,120
And she showed me this.

112
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:00,460
Let me see.

113
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:05,600
Goodness. Wait, this necklace is...

114
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:09,230
This is the necklace I gave to my wife.

115
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:11,540
She said she's had it
ever since she entered the orphanage.

116
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:17,340
It's her. It's really her.

117
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:21,250
This is my Eun Hye!

118
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:25,620
First, we have to find that USB.

119
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,190
But where could it possibly be?

120
00:07:27,490 --> 00:07:29,220
If we can just find that USB,

121
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,820
do you really think
we can find the wrench?

122
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:35,160
I think Seo Rin saved
important clues on it.

123
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:36,760
I have a feeling...

124
00:07:37,090 --> 00:07:39,760
that she knows something
but is hiding it on purpose.

125
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,700
I just can't figure Seo Rin out.

126
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:44,800
Maybe she's just scared of Chae Hwa Young.

127
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,200
You could be right.

128
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:48,610
Chae Hwa Young has controlled her
for a long time.

129
00:07:52,140 --> 00:07:53,280
Did you hear the news?

130
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:55,110
My father, I mean...

131
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:57,850
I think the Chairman
has found his daughter.

132
00:07:58,820 --> 00:07:59,950
- What did you say?
- What?

133
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,450
Where is my Eun Hye now?

134
00:08:02,450 --> 00:08:04,820
We've ordered a rush DNA test.

135
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:08,330
I thought it best for you to meet her
once we're absolutely sure.

136
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:11,360
You should have just told her to come.

137
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:15,470
How has my Eun Hye been living?
Tell me everything.

138
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:19,740
She's been struggling,
working at a restaurant in Incheon.

139
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:21,610
Oh, dear.

140
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:25,080
Oh, my Eun Hye...

141
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:27,550
She must have had such a hard life.

142
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,280
Goodness...

143
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:32,350
So what Mom said was true.
Grandfather really had a daughter.

144
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,850
A restaurant? Shit.

145
00:08:35,090 --> 00:08:36,690
She came to see Father?

146
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,200
Hello, is this the Boston Medical Center?

147
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,270
Yes, go ahead.

148
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:51,000
Let me check the schedule,
and I'll get back to you.

149
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:54,940
Seo Rin's hospital?

150
00:08:55,270 --> 00:08:59,010
Yes, they said Director Ma Seo Rin's
skin regeneration surgery was possible.

151
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:01,250
It's possible?

152
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:04,450
They want to schedule it right away.
What should I tell them?

153
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:08,150
What terrible timing...

154
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:15,060
Tell them to put that on hold for now.

155
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:16,730
On hold, sir?

156
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:20,830
All I can think about right now
is our Eun Hye.

157
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:22,700
With Seo Rin's surgery schedule,

158
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:25,200
I can't deal with the stress of traveling
to and from the US.

159
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:29,540
First, find Eun Hye and bring her to me.

160
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:32,410
We'll postpone Seo Rin's surgery
until after that.

161
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:35,110
- Do that.
- Yes, sir.

162
00:09:35,210 --> 00:09:37,620
And one more thing...

163
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:42,390
Don't let Seo Rin or Chae Hwa Young
know about us finding Eun Hye.

164
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,860
Father, you have a visitor.

165
00:09:50,230 --> 00:09:52,400
A visitor? Who is it?

166
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:55,270
She says she's your daughter.

167
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:57,970
My daughter?

168
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:17,190
Father?

169
00:10:17,890 --> 00:10:19,890
You're my father, right?

170
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,490
Father.

171
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:25,860
- Father.
- Shit.

172
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,430
This is ridiculous.

173
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:31,740
Are you really my daughter, Eun Hye?

174
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:32,870
Yes.

175
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:35,140
Chairman, the DNA test results
aren't back yet...

176
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:38,410
What do the results matter?

177
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:42,350
I've been wearing this necklace
since I got to the orphanage.

178
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:47,020
The director of the orphanage was sure
it was from my parents,

179
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:51,120
and she urged me to cherish it
my whole life, Father.

180
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:55,590
This necklace proves I'm your daughter.
What else could matter?

181
00:10:56,230 --> 00:11:00,060
- Father, I missed you so much.
- Alright.

182
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:04,370
Yes, let me see that necklace.

183
00:11:10,610 --> 00:11:11,610
A necklace?

184
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:20,990
I haven't seen that necklace before.
Where did you get it?

185
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:25,360
Go away, you thief!
This necklace is Suk Hee's.

186
00:11:27,590 --> 00:11:28,590
By the way,

187
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:33,200
is it really true
that you're the chairman of Dream Group?

188
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:38,240
The inscription is missing.

189
00:11:38,940 --> 00:11:39,940
An inscription?

190
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,310
She's not her.

191
00:11:41,710 --> 00:11:43,410
What? What do you mean?

192
00:11:44,310 --> 00:11:45,310
You...

193
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:47,910
are not my daughter Eun Hye.

194
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,650
- You're not her.
- I'm your daughter, Father!

195
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:52,250
- Secretary Kim.
- This necklace is the proof!

196
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,920
Give this woman some cab fare
and see her out.

197
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:58,520
- Father!
- Please, ma'am.

198
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:02,860
Father! Let me go!

199
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,600
There's an inscription on the necklace?

200
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,870
What in the world does it say?

201
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,200
Manager Lee.

202
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:13,340
I need you to look into that phony,
Park Young Mi.

203
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,470
Secretary Kim just dragged her out.

204
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:17,510
Find out where she lives, too.

205
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:23,280
Honey, here, drink some water
and compose yourself.

206
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:33,060
Can you believe that woman found out
you're the chairman of Dream Group...

207
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:36,660
and barged right into the house
before the DNA results were even in?

208
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:37,800
The nerve of her!

209
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:43,370
I'm absolutely speechless.

210
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:46,340
This kind of thing is going to happen
all the time now.

211
00:12:46,540 --> 00:12:49,270
You need to brace yourself, honey.

212
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,940
Once they get a whiff
of your enormous fortune,

213
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:54,850
there won't be just one or two fakes
swarming around like flies.

214
00:12:55,810 --> 00:12:58,820
- You'll have to be careful, honey.
- Don't you "honey" me.

215
00:13:00,420 --> 00:13:03,220
My own flesh and blood could be alive
and have walked right through that door,

216
00:13:03,620 --> 00:13:04,990
and you're calling her a fly? A fake?

217
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,930
Shut that filthy mouth of yours right now.

218
00:13:08,290 --> 00:13:10,060
No, I was just...

219
00:13:11,430 --> 00:13:15,430
- I'm just trying to protect your fortune.
- Don't be ridiculous.

220
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:20,300
I invited Seong Hye for lunch
before she leaves for the US,

221
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:21,840
so just get the table ready tomorrow.

222
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:25,940
I'm being ridiculous?
They'll be swarming in like flies.

223
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:34,020
Where's Grandfather?
I heard he found his long-lost daughter.

224
00:13:34,650 --> 00:13:36,650
Turns out she was a fake, so she's gone.

225
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:39,190
Father is so heartbroken, he's resting.

226
00:13:39,190 --> 00:13:40,390
A fake?

227
00:13:40,990 --> 00:13:43,090
She's got some nerve,
pulling a stunt like that.

228
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:44,500
Oh Jang Mi,

229
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:47,630
you should probably stop being
so high and mighty yourself.

230
00:13:48,170 --> 00:13:51,340
Things are fine for now,
but once they find your aunt,

231
00:13:51,570 --> 00:13:54,870
you and Seo Rin will be knocked
way down the pecking order.

232
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:57,810
- Serves you right.
- You're one to talk.

233
00:13:58,410 --> 00:14:00,510
Aren't you the one who should
get kicked out of this house?

234
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:04,880
You're not family, and you're not even
Grandfather's real daughter-in-law.

235
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,020
Why should I?

236
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:08,690
I'm the one who built Dream up
for the last 30 years.

237
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:12,590
The Chairman would have a harder time
getting rid of me than you.

238
00:14:12,990 --> 00:14:14,020
Just look at the situation.

239
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:17,130
Even after everything that's happened,
he still keeps me by his side.

240
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:21,000
The Chairman values results
over blood ties.

241
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:23,900
- You didn't know?
- That's just your opinion.

242
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,670
I will stop at nothing
to uncover your crimes,

243
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:29,770
make you face justice not just from him,
but from the entire world.

244
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,740
It'll happen soon, Chae Hwa Young.

245
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:33,810
Talk is cheap.

246
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:36,950
And snap out of it, Oh Jang Mi.

247
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:40,120
Right now, you and I are in the same boat.

248
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:45,120
If the Chairman finds his daughter,
both of us will be on the outs with him.

249
00:14:51,930 --> 00:14:54,530
Chae Hwa Young,
you're the one in trouble, not me.

250
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:08,950
Where on earth is that lipstick?

251
00:15:10,980 --> 00:15:11,980
Wait a minute...

252
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:14,550
What if Oh Jang Mi took it
and is just playing innocent?

253
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:16,690
No, that's not it.

254
00:15:16,990 --> 00:15:20,460
If she had, it would be game over by now.
There's no way she'd be this quiet.

255
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,260
Darn it.

256
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:25,900
I need that as my insurance policy.
It's the only leverage I have.

257
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:33,200
Seo Rin, I'm here.

258
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,270
I'm not happy to see you at all,
so get out.

259
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,910
I came to talk about something.

260
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:39,740
You heard, right? About finding our aunt.

261
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:41,280
I don't care.

262
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:45,350
Still, we'll be meeting her soon,
so you should be prepared.

263
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,880
You must be thrilled.

264
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:49,390
Even if Grandfather gives all our shares
to our new aunt,

265
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:51,290
you can just wrap her around
your little finger.

266
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,960
How can you say that?

267
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:56,730
You and Grandfather are more important
to me than Dream.

268
00:15:57,160 --> 00:16:00,960
I'm just so thankful that I got to meet
you and Grandfather.

269
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,370
Well, look who's playing the angel.

270
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:08,510
You're only human.
How could you not be interested in money?

271
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,440
You're greedy when it comes to men, too,
aren't you?

272
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,840
Juggling Kang Jun Ho and Kang Baek Ho,

273
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:15,880
weighing your options between them.

274
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:18,750
Ma Seo Rin, what is wrong with you?

275
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:22,420
I'm only like this because I'm worried
you're going down the wrong path.

276
00:16:22,490 --> 00:16:26,590
Especially Chae Hwa Young.
I'm worried she's manipulating you.

277
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:27,830
I'm begging you,

278
00:16:28,090 --> 00:16:30,830
- don't trust that woman so much.
- I'll handle my own business.

279
00:16:31,230 --> 00:16:33,830
Stop with your pathetic big sister act.
It's disgusting.

280
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:36,730
I'll stop for now
since Baek Ho gave a warning,

281
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,300
but you really need to be careful
of Chae Hwa Young.

282
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:43,370
When our aunt is found,
she'll do anything using you as a pawn.

283
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:46,180
Please, snap out of it, Ma Seo Rin.

284
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:48,510
This is a time
when we need to stick together,

285
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:50,980
so let's not waste our energy
fighting like this, okay?

286
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:03,060
I've had enough of this.
I have my own plans, you know.

287
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:05,860
I'm Ma Seo Rin.
Do you think I'm some kind of idiot?

288
00:17:13,540 --> 00:17:15,310
Please, don't let it be Jung Suk Hee.

289
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:20,710
(Honors Genetic Research Institute)

290
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:28,690
(DNA Comparison Test Results)

291
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:33,790
(Match)

292
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:35,560
(The DNAs of "Ma Dae Chang"
and "Jung Suk Hee" show...)

293
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,260
(a 99.99 percent
parent-child relationship.)

294
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:39,460
Impossible.

295
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:42,470
Chairman Ma and Jung Suk Hee
are father and daughter?

296
00:17:43,030 --> 00:17:44,870
So Chairman Ma Dae Chang
and Jung Suk Hee...

297
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,140
are really father and daughter?

298
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:49,510
It says 99.99 percent.

299
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:53,040
That's what it says.
A confirmed biological relationship.

300
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:56,680
Jung Suk Hee...

301
00:17:57,450 --> 00:17:59,080
That half-wit brat...

302
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:03,620
is Chairman Ma's real daughter.
How is this possible?

303
00:18:03,820 --> 00:18:04,820
Then...

304
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:06,760
does this mean everything we've planned...

305
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:09,790
has all been for nothing?

306
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:16,230
The empire I worked so hard to build...

307
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:18,600
was just a house of cards.

308
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,470
Chairman Ma's real heir...

309
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:25,180
was that half-wit, Jung Suk Hee.

310
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:30,150
This is a dire situation.

311
00:18:31,350 --> 00:18:34,180
If Chairman Ma acknowledges Jung Suk Hee
as his daughter,

312
00:18:36,290 --> 00:18:37,890
what will happen to you, ma'am?

313
00:18:38,190 --> 00:18:41,120
I ruined Jung Suk Hee and stole Seo Rin.

314
00:18:42,390 --> 00:18:45,100
On top of that, I got Oh Bok Gil killed.

315
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:48,370
He won't let me get away with it.
And the same goes for you.

316
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:53,140
What are we going to do?
Kang Hyuk, say something.

317
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:55,140
How are we going to survive this?

318
00:18:57,310 --> 00:19:00,710
Chairman Ma has launched a massive search
for his daughter.

319
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:05,020
Secretary Kim is searching every orphanage
in Incheon.

320
00:19:05,780 --> 00:19:08,290
Sooner or later,
they're going to find the records...

321
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:11,360
from the orphanage where Jung Suk Hee
stayed as a child.

322
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:14,120
We can't let that happen.
Before those records surface...

323
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:16,260
Before Chairman Ma gets his hands
on that list,

324
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:18,130
we have to make our move.

325
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,600
<i>- Three little bears</i>
<i>- Three bears</i>

326
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:24,670
<i>- Lived in a house</i>
<i>- In a house</i>

327
00:19:24,970 --> 00:19:29,110
<i>- Papa Bear, Mama Bear, and Baby Bear</i>
<i>- Baby Bear</i>

328
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:33,140
<i>- Papa Bear is so chubby</i>
<i>- So chubby</i>

329
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:40,750
Kang Hyuk.

330
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:44,120
I found a way out for us.

331
00:19:44,420 --> 00:19:47,090
Really? What is it?

332
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,930
I never considered Ma Dong Seok.

333
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:52,960
What's Ma Dong Seok's story again?

334
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,270
Come to think of it,

335
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:58,270
doesn't that make him
and Jung Suk Hee siblings?

336
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,140
That means they were lovers and siblings.

337
00:20:02,940 --> 00:20:05,010
And on top of that,
they had children together.

338
00:20:05,980 --> 00:20:07,810
My gosh, how could this happen?

339
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:10,310
What do you think would happen
if I told Chairman Ma about this?

340
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:11,980
What are you planning to do?

341
00:20:12,580 --> 00:20:15,450
Wouldn't he prefer our Jun Ho
over that tainted bloodline?

342
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:20,220
I'm getting all of Seo Rin's shares.

343
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:23,730
And then, I'll approach
the board members first...

344
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:25,930
and drop this bombshell on them.

345
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:28,600
Ma Dong Seok and Jung Suk Hee
were siblings,

346
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:31,230
and they had twins together.

347
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:32,540
If that happens,

348
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:35,910
Chairman Ma, Seo Rin,
Jung Suk Hee, and Oh Jang Mi...

349
00:20:37,310 --> 00:20:38,940
will all be socially ruined.

350
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:41,980
Exactly. We get what we want
without getting our hands dirty.

351
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:44,050
This plan just might work.

352
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:46,920
I will return to my rightful place.

353
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:49,990
Fate is always on my side.

354
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:53,120
You keep this safe.

355
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:55,460
There are rats everywhere, so be careful.

356
00:20:55,930 --> 00:20:56,930
Understood.

357
00:20:58,630 --> 00:20:59,630
But...

358
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,270
I wonder why Dong Seok isn't
in the family pictures.

359
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:06,840
He's definitely older than Jung Suk Hee.

360
00:21:08,870 --> 00:21:11,240
So, that fake daughter is gone?

361
00:21:11,580 --> 00:21:13,940
Yes. She put on quite a show.

362
00:21:14,850 --> 00:21:16,080
What a relief, though.

363
00:21:16,350 --> 00:21:19,350
If Chairman Ma's real daughter
actually shows up,

364
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:21,650
we'll be left with nothing.

365
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:23,920
Mom, now that I think about it,

366
00:21:24,820 --> 00:21:27,490
it might be a good thing
if Chairman Ma finds his daughter.

367
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:30,060
What? No, he can't find her!

368
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:32,800
If Chairman Ma's daughter comes,
she'll be the one in charge.

369
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,900
All we have to do is get on her good side.

370
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:37,870
- What?
- If Chairman Ma's daughter comes,

371
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:39,370
Chae Hwa Young will be out of the picture.

372
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,570
Besides, Seo Rin and Jang Mi
will get knocked down a peg.

373
00:21:43,340 --> 00:21:46,280
We just need to make sure
we side with the real daughter.

374
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:48,980
Oh my, you're right.

375
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:53,950
Come to think of it,
I'd be her stepmother.

376
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:56,490
- Right, Hong Ju?
- That's what I'm saying.

377
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:58,790
This could actually be
a better situation for us.

378
00:22:00,690 --> 00:22:01,690
You're right.

379
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:04,730
We have no reason
to be wringing our hands over this.

380
00:22:05,700 --> 00:22:07,000
Since Seong Hye,

381
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,630
the chairman's sister-in-law,
is coming tomorrow,

382
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:13,240
I'll have to show her exactly
who she's dealing with.

383
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:18,880
I'm going to Suk Hee's
to stock up on side dishes.

384
00:22:20,740 --> 00:22:22,450
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

385
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:24,880
Come on, Tae Pyung. Am I wrong?

386
00:22:25,050 --> 00:22:28,150
We're talking about a daughter
he lost almost half a century ago.

387
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:30,520
How in the world is he supposed
to find her now?

388
00:22:30,820 --> 00:22:33,120
He might find her if it's meant to be.

389
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:35,430
Find her? I doubt it.

390
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:39,100
Just today, some shabby-looking woman
came crawling out of the woodwork,

391
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:43,530
claiming to be his real daughter
and crying a river.

392
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:48,110
They're just parasites who smelled money.

393
00:22:48,110 --> 00:22:49,170
Total parasites.

394
00:22:51,140 --> 00:22:52,510
Not a parasite.

395
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:54,880
I don't like parasites.

396
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:59,580
Suk Hee, stay out of it.
Stop talking nonsense.

397
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:01,490
Go away, you twisted donut lady.

398
00:23:02,050 --> 00:23:05,490
Stop bothering my Tae Pyung!

399
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:08,290
My goodness,
she always has to get the last word.

400
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:12,660
Suk Hee, when did you get so chatty?

401
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:18,270
But technology has gotten
so much better these days.

402
00:23:18,570 --> 00:23:22,640
You can register your DNA with the police,
and they might find a match right away.

403
00:23:22,810 --> 00:23:26,380
Please. He already gave
blood samples ages ago...

404
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,650
and registered his DNA.

405
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:29,880
He already did?

406
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:34,350
- And you haven't heard anything?
- It hasn't been that long,

407
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:37,890
but since we didn't hear back right away,
I'm 100 percent sure she's dead.

408
00:23:38,190 --> 00:23:39,990
You never know. Just wait and see.

409
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:45,560
Maybe I should get my mom's DNA
registered with the police, just in case.

410
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:47,930
Right. What am I thinking?

411
00:23:48,230 --> 00:23:51,170
I came for the side dishes,

412
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,340
but I was also hoping
you could lend me a hand.

413
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,340
Lend you a hand? Whose hand?

414
00:23:57,570 --> 00:23:58,980
My mom?

415
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:05,420
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

416
00:24:08,590 --> 00:24:09,590
Mom.

417
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:15,390
- Why is there so much?
- These are for Grandfather.

418
00:24:15,530 --> 00:24:18,260
And the bracelet is a gift, too.

419
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:22,530
Goodness. You made so much.

420
00:24:23,830 --> 00:24:25,970
That's good. Geum Soon was saying
it was hard for her...

421
00:24:25,970 --> 00:24:28,870
to make the right side dishes
because of Grandfather's blood pressure.

422
00:24:28,940 --> 00:24:31,880
Suk Hee wants to be friends
with Grandfather.

423
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:34,180
I like Grandfather.

424
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:39,150
Mom, let's take this
and give it to Grandfather in person.

425
00:24:39,550 --> 00:24:43,950
No. Grandfather will get mad.

426
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:48,060
No, he won't.
Grandfather isn't mad at you anymore.

427
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:51,930
Plus, you made him this bracelet,
so give it to him yourself.

428
00:24:51,930 --> 00:24:52,960
It's a gift, right?

429
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:04,980
It looks like I won't get to see Eun Hye
before I go back to the US.

430
00:25:06,510 --> 00:25:08,380
I was hoping against hope.

431
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:12,650
We knew we wouldn't find her quickly.

432
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:15,120
Just wait a little longer.

433
00:25:16,220 --> 00:25:17,790
I promise I'll have good news for you.

434
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,960
Okay, I will.

435
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:25,900
Dinner is ready.

436
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:29,730
Alright, let's go eat.

437
00:25:30,230 --> 00:25:31,300
Okay.

438
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,160
What is this?

439
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:55,190
Why are you two in my house?

440
00:25:56,530 --> 00:25:57,630
I asked, why are you here?

441
00:25:58,430 --> 00:25:59,700
It's the thief! The thief!

442
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:03,630
The nerve of you, calling this your house
when you're the one squatting here.

443
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,540
How is this your house?
It belongs to my grandfather.

444
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:07,670
Exactly.

445
00:26:08,170 --> 00:26:11,940
Why are you in someone else's kitchen
and making yourselves at home?

446
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:26,260
- Jang Mi.
- Have a seat, Grandfather.

447
00:26:27,790 --> 00:26:28,890
Hello.

448
00:26:29,230 --> 00:26:30,360
Hello there.

449
00:26:30,860 --> 00:26:32,060
Is that CEO Chae's daughter?

450
00:26:32,630 --> 00:26:33,960
Right, Seong Hye.

451
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:36,570
Say hello. This is your great-aunt.

452
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,440
Hello, it's nice to meet you.

453
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:42,870
Yes, of course.
Goodness, you are a pretty one.

454
00:26:42,870 --> 00:26:44,110
Let's sit down.

455
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:49,550
She insisted on making soybean paste stew
for you, Grandfather.

456
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:52,520
I see.

457
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:55,590
Suk Hee makes a tasty soybean paste stew.

458
00:26:55,590 --> 00:26:57,050
It'll just be a minute.

459
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:04,930
You've got to be kidding me.

460
00:27:05,460 --> 00:27:08,700
What if that's the necklace
Father said he gave her?

461
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,800
I can't let Father see that,
no matter what.

462
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:18,140
Careful.

463
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:26,820
(Chang)

464
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:39,200
(Chang)

465
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:01,180
(The First Man)

466
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:04,690
I can't believe that kind woman
is Jang Mi's mother.

467
00:28:05,260 --> 00:28:06,560
The thief is back!

468
00:28:06,620 --> 00:28:08,390
What do you think you're doing
to Jang Mi's mother?

469
00:28:08,530 --> 00:28:10,330
Of all people, why is Jun Ho here now?

470
00:28:10,690 --> 00:28:13,630
- Hwa Young, let's run away.
- Are you crazy?

471
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:17,770
I want to live as a real family
with you and my son, Jun Ho.

472
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:19,000
I have something for you.

473
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:22,170
Do you think this evidence will be enough
to corner Chae Hwa Young?

474
00:28:22,470 --> 00:28:24,670
We have to make sure
she has no way out this time.

475
00:28:29,210 --> 00:28:31,210
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
